DATABASE MANAGEMENT SYSTEM
Database management systems (DBMSs) are specially designed
software applications that interact with the user, other applications,
and the database itself to capture and analyse data. A general purpose DBMS is a software system designed to allow the definition,
creation, querying, update, and administration of databases.
